<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-18T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3441: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hull</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-18T14:00:00-03:00">December 18, 1933—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 18—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>66. Entire Committee approves of and wishes to take final action tomorrow
                            morning on proposed declaration in my 64, December 18, noon.</p>
                        <p>Can we hear from you immediately?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>